        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="TvdYabubaMgP4hZpLByh-3" style="edgeStyle=orthogonalEdgeStyle;rounded=0;orthogonalLoop=1;jettySize=auto;html=1;entryX=1;entryY=0.5;entryDx=0;entryDy=0;" parent="1" source="TvdYabubaMgP4hZpLByh-2" target="Gi5KEacH5U4bPrpyxMOf-1" edge="1">
          <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="TvdYabubaMgP4hZpLByh-2" value="I&#39;m not convinced I need this yet.. I might be able to solve the issue by making FileOutputWriter and StandardOutputWriter thread safe&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;I&#39;ll implement this last.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;I&#39;ve been doing research and actually it looks like this might not be necessary. It would be a top-level bottleneck. Instead the writer itself will manage thread interaction using mutex / lock&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Dedicated logging thread (high-performance systems)&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Producers push messages into a lock-free queue&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Single background thread writes to disk&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Zero contention on I/O&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="shape=note2;boundedLbl=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;size=25;verticalAlign=top;align=center;" parent="1" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="620" y="55" width="310" height="310" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="TvdYabubaMgP4hZpLByh-5" value="&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-top:4px;text-align:center;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;LogConfigurations&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr size=&quot;1&quot; style=&quot;border-style:solid;&quot;&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-left:4px;&quot;&gt;- default_: LogConfiguration&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-left:4px;&quot;&gt;- configurations_ : vector&amp;lt;LogConfiguration&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr size=&quot;1&quot; style=&quot;border-style:solid;&quot;&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-left:4px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;+ LogConfigurations()&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-left:4px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;+ LogConfigurations(defaultConfiguration: LogConfiguration)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0px 0px 0px 4px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;+ log(source: std::type_index, level: LogLevel, message: std::string)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0px 0px 0px 4px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;+ add(logConfiguration: LogConfiguration) : void&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0px 0px 0px 4px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;+ clear() : void&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;" style="verticalAlign=top;align=left;overflow=fill;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;" parent="1" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="-144" y="710" width="397" height="150" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="skFjbr4E7Fnc3YblYDC3-4" style="edgeStyle=orthogonalEdgeStyle;rounded=0;orthogonalLoop=1;jettySize=auto;html=1;entryX=0;entryY=0.5;entryDx=0;entryDy=0;endArrow=none;endFill=0;" parent="1" source="TvdYabubaMgP4hZpLByh-6" target="Gi5KEacH5U4bPrpyxMOf-2" edge="1">
          <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="TvdYabubaMgP4hZpLByh-6" value="&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;TODO:&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;Finish off propagating the source down&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;Logger can be duplicated many times - it must be lightwight - would the Flyweight pattern apply here?" style="shape=note2;boundedLbl=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;size=25;verticalAlign=top;align=center;" parent="1" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="-650" y="407.5" width="305" height="135" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="skFjbr4E7Fnc3YblYDC3-3" style="edgeStyle=orthogonalEdgeStyle;rounded=0;orthogonalLoop=1;jettySize=auto;html=1;entryX=0;entryY=0.5;entryDx=0;entryDy=0;endArrow=none;endFill=0;" parent="1" source="skFjbr4E7Fnc3YblYDC3-2" target="TvdYabubaMgP4hZpLByh-5" edge="1">
          <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="skFjbr4E7Fnc3YblYDC3-2" value="Implement this as a normal class that the consumer will reference by const reference&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;const LogConfigurations&amp;amp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;We&#39;ll move synchronisation further down the chain to enhance performance (reads don&#39;t require locks)&lt;/div&gt;" style="shape=note2;boundedLbl=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;size=25;verticalAlign=top;align=center;" parent="1" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="-690" y="690" width="340" height="190" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="skFjbr4E7Fnc3YblYDC3-5" value="&lt;b&gt;Problem!&lt;/b&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;I don&#39;t want to have to pass around the LogConfiguration reference to every instance of Logger.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;i style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;Thought:&lt;/i&gt;&amp;nbsp;With a Singleton I wouldn&#39;t have to. I&#39;d just call getInstance and be provided with the instance from anywhere in the application&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;i style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;Decision:&lt;/i&gt;&amp;nbsp;This will only require me to have one single constructor. The sources will be referenced, not passed in. I also then don&#39;t think this will qualify as &quot;composition&quot;&lt;/div&gt;" style="shape=note2;boundedLbl=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;size=25;verticalAlign=top;align=center;" parent="1" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="630" y="460" width="270" height="260" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
