        <mxCell id="xFbWbN_iQ98PUsdl_pN4-2" value="&lt;b&gt;11/02/2026&lt;/b&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Singleton is considered a code smell in modern C++&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;To this extent the solution is to have LogConfigurations be created as a single instance by the application and then pass it as a constant reference.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;const LogConfigurations&amp;amp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;is how this will look inside the Logger&lt;/div&gt;" style="shape=note2;boundedLbl=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;size=25;verticalAlign=top;align=center;" parent="1" vertex="1">
